DOM (DOCUMENT OBJECT MODEL )

--- it is used in web development used to interact and manipulate (Change) the html documents.
When the webpages loaded, the browser created DOM of the webpage.
When the html file is loaded into the browser,the javascript cannot understand the html document directly.
DOM : it is basically the representation of the same html document but in a tree like structure composed of object .

Key points :
1)	Structure : the dom represent the structure of html document as a tree each node in tree represents the elements , an attributes or text .
2)	Manipulation : using javascript you can interact with elements (buttons paragraphs) on the webpages , changing the context styles can add or remove elements 
3)	Event handling : you can handle the interactions like click or pressing the buttons
4)	Wc3 world wide web consortium.

	  
